The paper deals with an online optimization problem related to graphs and trees, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of primal-dual algorithms and analysis techniques suggests that it could also belong to the categories of information theory (cs.IT) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the focus on optimization and competitiveness suggests that it could belong to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
